Title: The effect of St John's wort on the pharmacokinetics of docetaxel.

Parameter: area under the docetaxel plasma concentration-time curve extrapolated to infinity (AUC∞)
Sentece: SJW supplementation resulted in a statistically significant decrease in the mean area under the docetaxel plasma concentration-time curve extrapolated to infinity (AUC∞) from 3,035 ± 756 to 2,682 ± 717 ng · h/mL (P = 0.045).

Sentece: Furthermore, docetaxel clearance significantly increased from 47.2 to 53.7 L/h (P = 0.045) after SJW intake.
Title: The effect of St John's wort on the pharmacokinetics of docetaxel.
Name: Hyperforin

Parameter: area under the concentration curve from 0 to 6 hours (AUC(0-6))
Sentece: After oral administration of the SJW-NE formulation (5.2 mg hyperforin/kg) in mice, higher hyperforin exposure in plasma (1188 ± 41 nM·h) and the brain (52.9 ± 1.6 pmol/g tissue·h) was observed with 2.8- and 1.3-fold increases of the area under the concentration curve from 0 to 6 hours (AUC(0-6)) compared to those of the SJW extract (417 ± 41 nM·h in plasma and 41.6 ± 1.5 pmol/g tissue·h in the brain).
Title: In vitro and in vivo characterization of new formulations of St. John's Wort extract with improved pharmacokinetics and anti-nociceptive effect.
Name: Hyperforin
